b.span: Notes on one-off configurations to remember:

div.style: text-align: left

span.font: FTP Pasv Mode/Port Forwarding : During kickstart process a local ftp repo is being read by the RHCE* VM's and connections were timing out when packets were being routed via the bridge interface br_fe through the router (192.168.2.1) and due to NAT'ing and Firewall these were getting dropped. Two w/a applied to circumvent this issue

div.style: text-align: left
div.span: a) Added rich-rules to allow all subnets, including the LAN, default virtual subnet and custom created ones.

div.style: text-align: left
div.span: rule family="ipv4" source address="192.168.123.0/24" log prefix="ftp_firewalld" level="info" accept

div.style: text-align: left
div.span: b) Configured on vsftp.conf to have the ports with set defined range so to do the port forwarding via router.
